name: NPR
text:
Tropical Cyclone Gati has made landfall in Somalia, where it's expected to drop two years' worth of rain in the next two days. It's the first recorded instance of a hurricane-strength system hitting the country. 
https://t.co/tnf7LxAE5m

name: NPR
text: Most presidents spend their final weeks in office trying to cement their legacies. But Trump's tactics since he lost to Biden have raised alarms that he's doing damage to confidence in free and fair elections. https://t.co/vPuXoMr3On

name: NPR
text: Kasich, a 2016 Republican presidential candidate, told NPR that Biden "has clearly won this election and it is just sort of amazing to me that Republicans just keep sitting on their hands. It makes no sense." https://t.co/AVALJHaDc2

name: NPR
text:
We asked you if there's a woman in your community who's overcome great challenges in their personal lives during the pandemic. You responded with more than 50 nominations.

So, here are 7 women who have found the strength to pull through: https://t.co/yE8slBuwd2

name: NPR
text:
Lebanon's ancient cedar trees are a source of national pride. But climate change has brought their very survival into question, as rising temperatures fuel growing threats from wildfires and insect infestations.
https://t.co/crch1tv9fX

name: NPR
text: A 12-year-old German pro soccer fan has been building detailed lego reconstructions of their stadiums without the help of blueprints. https://t.co/wtzXewn45M

text:

"Mary Ellen could see a story in the ordinary that you might just walk by and not even see."
https://t.co/VnF3ztrMb7

text:

 https://t.co/zYrShSrFQE

name: NPR
text:
Jasmine Surti is a problem solver. So for her socially-distanced Thanksgiving, she found a way that 6 households across 2 states could eat their favorite foods, made by loved ones.

"I created a map of how we're going to get the food where it needs to go."
https://t.co/L9sVfc276D

text:

text:

Blinken served as deputy secretary of state and deputy national security adviser under President Obama.

text:
When the state of Kansas issued a mask mandate, 81 counties opted out. Researchers found that coronavirus infection rates rose sharply in the opt-out counties — while falling in areas that required masks.

text:

Saudi Arabia's government has denied the reports.

name: NPR
text:

name: NPR
text: More than 150 business leaders are calling on President Trump to concede the election, saying the stalled transition is hurting the country's reputation and impeding efforts to revitalize the pandemic-ravaged economy. https://t.co/F5QtcQYrPU
